        author of Gaul in the second half of the 5th cent. AD b. on 5 November 430/431 in Lug(u)dunum 
        (present-day Lyons)...."</mads:note>
    <mads:note type="source">His Carmina, 1982: t.p. (Sidonio Apollinare) p. 15 (Caio Sollio 
      Apollinare Sidonio; b. in Lyons bet. 430 and 432; m. Papianilla, after serving Emperor, appointed 
      bp. of Clermont-Ferrand in 471, d. ca. 486, sainted soon thereafter)</mads:note>
